  "slug": "roasted-squash-pancetta-risotto",
  "title": "Roasted Squash & Pancetta Risotto",
  "subtitle": "Patience, a wooden spoon, and a ladle of warm stock.",
  "excerpt": "Roasted Squash & Pancetta Risotto. A classic risotto built the slow way: stock warm beside you, ladle by ladle, until the grains are creamy with a bite.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "From Rebecca's personal cookbook, with a method that follows the classical Italian risotto canon, stock warm beside the rice, ladled in slowly, finished with cold butter and grated parmesan.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Roasted Squash & Pancetta Risotto. The dish belongs to the Italian home-cooking register: straightforward, ingredient-led, calm at the hob. Adjustable for what you need.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Stock kept warm beside you, rice toasted, wine in, ladle by ladle until the grains are soft with a bite at the centre. No need to stir constantly, gently, often.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
